10 provisions, a fine not more than Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00)
11 upon the second conviction for violation of any of such provisions,
12 and a fine not more than Seven Thousand Five Hundred Dollars
13 ($7,500.00) upon the third or subsequent convictions for violation
14 of any of such provisions, or by both such imprisonment and fine.
15 In addition, the court may require a term of community service not
16 less than forty (40) hours nor more than eighty (80) hours. The
17 court in which any such conviction is had shall notify the county
18 superintendent of public health of such conviction.
19 E. Any person violating paragraph 4 of subsection A of Section
20 1029 of this title shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a Class B4
21 felony offense and shall be punished in accordance with the
